cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper proposes a new method for binary neural networks that improves accuracy while reducing memory consumption and inference speed. The method is evaluated on image classification and detection tasks, indicating a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a weight balanced binarization technique and a gated residual to compensate for information loss, suggesting a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper proposes a generic network module that can be applied to various network architectures, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM).
